{
  "chapterIndex": 3,
  "pageIndex": 9,
  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "They stepped off the trolley into a part of the city that felt older than the rest."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Narrow streets.\n\nBrick buildings worn smooth by time.\n\nSmall storefronts tucked into corners like they had always been there and had no intention of leaving."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra led again, but slower this time."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Not pulling him forward.\n\nJust walking… and letting him follow beside her."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "There’s a place up here. It’s not impressive, so don’t expect too much."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That sounds like a warning."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "It’s a disclaimer."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "For what?"
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "For the fact that I like it."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan smiled faintly."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That’s enough for me."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "She looked at him for a second longer than necessary."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Then turned forward again."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "The stand was small."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Barely more than a window in the wall with a handwritten menu taped beside it."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra leaned in, reading."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Okay. You’re trying something new."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That feels like a decision I should be part of."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "You are. You’re agreeing with me."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan laughed quietly."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That doesn’t feel like agreement."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "It’s trust."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That feels worse."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "She grinned and ordered anyway."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "A few minutes later, she handed him something wrapped in paper."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Don’t overthink it."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "He took it, their fingers brushing again."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "This time—\n\nhe didn’t pull back immediately.\n\nNeither did she."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Just a second.\n\nLong enough to feel it.\n\nShort enough to pretend it didn’t happen."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan looked down at the food."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "What is it?"
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Try it."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That’s not an answer."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "It’s a better experience."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "He took a bite."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Paused."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Then looked at her."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "That’s actually really good."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "I know."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "You say that like you made it."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "I chose it. That counts."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan nodded slowly."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "I think that’s how you see everything."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "How?"
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Ethan",
      "content": "Like choosing something gives it meaning."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Cassandra tilted her head slightly."
    },
    {
      "type": "dialogue",
      "character": "Cassandra",
      "content": "Doesn’t it?"
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Ethan didn’t answer right away."
    },
    {
      "type": "narration",
      "content": "Because the question didn’t feel simple."
    }
  ]
}